A fight between two groups of men from two villages in Mount Ayliff, in the Eastern Cape, has left at least seven people dead. Six others have been rushed to hospital. It's believed that a group of around ten men, from Mpheni village allegedly attacked another group from Nokhatshile village. JOHANNESBURG - A fight between two groups in Mount Ayliff, in the Eastern Cape, has left at least seven people dead. Six others have been rushed to hospital. It's believed that a group of ten men from Mpheni village allegedly attacked another group from Nokhatshile village. READ:Â Almost 70 people arrested in Gauteng for various crimes According to police, the fight is about a dispute between local taxi associations. The provincial government has condemned the attack and is appealing to anyone with information to come forward.